Slovenia's transition from a tiny communist state in an authoritarian
communist Yugoslav federation to a fully independent market-oriented,
multi-party parliamentary democracy took place in the brief span of
just over three years (1988-1991). By 1994 the economic future was
murky, but Slovenia was clearly facing its challenges as a functioning
democracy.</SUM>
